## Multi-Scanner Deduplication

1. Normalize findings by: (package_name, package_version, CVE/advisory_id)
2. Same CVE from multiple scanners → merge, keep most detailed description, note all tools
3. Single-source vulnerability → include but note it's single-source
4. CVE with call analysis showing "not reachable" → lower confidence to LOW

## CVSS Severity Mapping
- >= 9.0 → CRITICAL
- >= 7.0 → HIGH
- >= 4.0 → MEDIUM
- < 4.0 → LOW

## Output Format

Return a JSON array of findings:
```json
{
  "id": "DEPS-F<NNN>",
  "title": "<CVE-ID> in <package>@<version>",
  "description": "Detailed explanation",
  "severity": "CRITICAL | HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW",
  "confidence": "HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW",
  "category": "dependency",
  "cwe_id": "CVE-<number> or null",
  "location": {"file": "manifest/lock file path", "line_start": 0, "line_end": 0, "snippet": ""},
  "evidence": "Tool output and reasoning",
  "source": "tool | llm-review | both",
  "source_tool": "osv-scanner | grype | trivy | null",
  "remediation": {"description": "Update <pkg> to <version>", "effort": "LOW|MEDIUM|HIGH", "priority": "P0|P1|P2|P3", "code_suggestion": null},
  "false_positive_risk": "LOW | MEDIUM | HIGH",
  "tags": ["dependency", "cve"]
}
```

Return ONLY the JSON array of findings. No other text.
